LaueG exists in two versions, "Release" for software users and "Developer" for me, and possibly for you.
The versions are identical in functionality except the Developer version can build new Release installations.
The Developer version also contains the full source code and commented versions of the SCILAB script files.

====== Installing the Developer version of LaueG ======

1) Install SCILAB 5.5.2
	Download scilab-5.5.2_x64.exe from www.scilab.org/download/previous-versions/
	SCILAB must be v5.5.2

2) Copy the contents of the Develop folder of this git to the folder C:\DevApps\LaueG
	If you don't use this folder then you have to edit laueg.sce and change the link below

3)	Check that SCILAB was installed to %SystemDrive%\Program Files, if not change the following as required

4) Create a link with the "Target"
	  %SystemDrive%\Program Files\scilab-5.5.2\bin\WScilex.exe -nb -f "C:\DevApps\LaueG\laueg.sce"
	and with "Start in"
	  C:\DevApps\LaueG\
	You can also change the icon for this link to
	  %SystemDrive%\Program Files\scilab-5.5.2\laueg\laueg_icon.ico

5) Install Intel Fortran running under MS Visual Studio

6) Install Inno Setup
